---
import CaseStudy from '../../layouts/CaseStudy.astro';
---
<CaseStudy slug="infinity">
  <Fragment slot="header">
    <div class="cs-hero">[Infinity — licensed CPG packaging lineup]</div>
    <div class="cs-tags"><span class="cs-tag">Brand</span><span class="cs-tag">Licensing</span><span class="cs-tag">CPG</span><span class="cs-tag">Packaging</span></div>
    <div class="cs-title">Infinity — Licensed CPG brand direction and packaging at scale</div>
    <div class="cs-subtitle">Creative Director at Infinity Lifestyle Brands. Led brand direction and packaging across a $10M+ licensed CPG portfolio spanning Disney, MLBPA, and Viacom IP — reconciling licensor guidelines with a coherent brand aesthetic across 50+ SKUs.</div>
    <div class="cs-meta-card">
      <div class="cs-meta-row"><div class="cs-meta-label">Client</div><div class="cs-meta-value">Infinity Lifestyle Brands</div></div>
      <div class="cs-meta-row"><div class="cs-meta-label">Duration</div><div class="cs-meta-value">2018 – 2019</div></div>
      <div class="cs-meta-row"><div class="cs-meta-label">Role</div><div class="cs-meta-value">Creative Director</div></div>
      <div class="cs-meta-row"><div class="cs-meta-label">Industry</div><div class="cs-meta-value">Licensed CPG</div></div>
    </div>
  </Fragment>

  <div class="section">
    <div class="stat-strip">
      <div class="stat-box"><div class="stat-num">$10M+</div><div class="stat-label">Licensing ecosystem supported</div></div>
      <div class="stat-box"><div class="stat-num">50+</div><div class="stat-label">SKUs shipped to retail</div></div>
      <div class="stat-box"><div class="stat-num">3</div><div class="stat-label">Major IP partners (Disney · MLBPA · Viacom)</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-label">Context · Action · Result</div>
    <div class="car-grid">
      <div class="car-sidebar">
        <div class="car-step active" onclick="switchCar(this,'car-infinity-1')"><div class="car-step-label">01 · Context</div><div class="car-step-title">The situation</div></div>
        <div class="car-step" onclick="switchCar(this,'car-infinity-2')"><div class="car-step-label">02 · Action</div><div class="car-step-title">What I did</div></div>
        <div class="car-step" onclick="switchCar(this,'car-infinity-3')"><div class="car-step-label">03 · Result</div><div class="car-step-title">What it produced</div></div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div id="car-infinity-1" class="car-content">
          <div class="car-content-label">01 · Context</div>
          <div class="car-content-title">A licensed CPG portfolio with multiple IP holders, strict brand guidelines, and no unifying creative direction.</div>
          <div class="car-content-body">Infinity built and distributed licensed consumer goods across major entertainment IPs — each licensor (Disney, MLBPA, Viacom) with its own style guide, approval cycles, and creative constraints. The portfolio needed a coherent aesthetic and operating system that could scale across 50+ SKUs while clearing every licensor review.</div>
        </div>
        <div id="car-infinity-2" class="car-content" style="display:none">
          <div class="car-content-label">02 · Action</div>
          <div class="car-content-title">Led creative direction across packaging, marketing, and trade execution.</div>
          <div class="car-content-body">Owned brand direction and packaging design end-to-end — style guides, packaging architecture, retail-ready artwork, and trade marketing assets. Managed licensor approval cycles across Disney, MLBPA, and Viacom, and built internal systems to scale brand consistency across a growing SKU count.</div>
        </div>
        <div id="car-infinity-3" class="car-content" style="display:none">
          <div class="car-content-label">03 · Result</div>
          <div class="car-content-title">$10M+ licensing ecosystem. 50+ SKUs. Three major IP partners cleared.</div>
          <div class="car-content-body">Creative cleared licensor review across all three major IP partners and supported a $10M+ licensing ecosystem. Shipped 50+ SKUs to retail with a unified brand direction, building the operating playbook for licensed CPG work carried into later consultancy engagements.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</CaseStudy>
